  <content>
    <description>
      <levelledPara id="HYD-SYS-OVERVIEW">
        <title>General</title>
        <para>The ATEST aircraft hydraulic power system supplies pressurized hydraulic
        fluid at 3000 PSI to operate the following systems:
        </para>
        <para>
          <sequentialList>
            <listItem><para>Landing gear extension and retraction system (ATA 32)</para></listItem>
            <listItem><para>Flight control actuation system (ATA 27)</para></listItem>
            <listItem><para>Wheel brake system (ATA 32)</para></listItem>
            <listItem><para>Nose wheel steering system (ATA 32)</para></listItem>
          </sequentialList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>

      <levelledPara id="HYD-PRV-DESC">
        <title>Pressure Regulator Valve (PRV)</title>
        <para>The Pressure Regulator Valve (PRV), Part Number HYD-PRV-3A (current)
        or HYD-PRV-4B (replacement per AMB HYD-2024-001), regulates hydraulic system
        pressure to 3000 PSI ±100 PSI nominal operating range.</para>
        <para>The PRV is located on the hydraulic power pack assembly behind Access
        Panel HYD-20 on the left side of the fuselage.</para>
        <para>
          <table>
            <tgroup cols="2">
              <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1*"/>
              <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="2*"/>
              <thead>
                <row><entry>Parameter</entry><entry>Value</entry></row>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <row><entry>Nominal pressure</entry><entry>3000 PSI</entry></row>
                <row><entry>Operating range</entry><entry>2900–3100 PSI</entry></row>
                <row><entry>Maximum pressure</entry><entry>3400 PSI (relief)</entry></row>
                <row><entry>Fluid specification</entry><entry>Mil-PRF-5606 (hydraulic oil, red)</entry></row>
                <row><entry>Current PRV P/N</entry><entry>HYD-PRV-3A</entry></row>
                <row><entry>Replacement PRV P/N</entry><entry>HYD-PRV-4B (per AMB HYD-2024-001)</entry></row>
              </tbody>
            </tgroup>
          </table>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>

      <levelledPara id="HYD-FLUID-SPEC">
        <title>Hydraulic Fluid</title>
        <para>The hydraulic system uses Mil-PRF-5606 mineral-based hydraulic fluid
        (coloured red for identification). The system capacity is 4.5 litres.
        Do not mix with phosphate ester fluids (Skydrol type). Mixing causes seal
        degradation and system failure.</para>
      </levelledPara>
    </description>
